            <title>[FLINK-35796] Ensure that MailboxExecutor.submit is used correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-35796</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-34470&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-34470&lt;/a&gt; showed that MailboxExecutor.submit may result in unexpected exception handling: while &lt;tt&gt;execute&lt;/tt&gt; will bubble up the exception in the task thread and result in some fault, &lt;tt&gt;submit&lt;/tt&gt; can hide the exception because the API assumes that the returned &lt;tt&gt;Future&lt;/tt&gt; is checked for it explicitly or implicitly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can solve the situation by improving the doc of MailboxExecutor and double-check the internal usages.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
